<em>Syrianus et la m&eacute;taphysique de l&rsquo;antiquit&eacute;
tardive</em>, A. Longo (ed.), Napoli: Bibliopolis, pp.
201&ndash;229.</li>

<li>Taormina, D. P., 1989, <em>Plutarco di Atene: l&rsquo;uno,
l&rsquo;anima, le forme</em>, Catania: CUECM.</li>

<li>Tar&aacute;n, L., 1987, &ldquo;Syrianus and
Pseudo-Alexander&rsquo;s commentary on <em>Metaph</em>. E-N&rdquo;, in
<em>Kommentierung, &Uuml;berlieferung, Nachleben</em>, J. Wiesner
(ed.), Berlin-Boston: De Gruyter, pp. 215&ndash;232.</li>

<li>Usener, H., 1961, <em>Aristotelis Opera</em>, ex recensione I.
Bekkeri edidit Academia Regia Borussica, t. IV: <em>Scholia in
Aristotelem</em> collegit C. A. Brandis, <em>Supplementum scholiorum:
Syriani In Metaphysica commentaria</em> ed. H. U., accedit <em>Vita
marciana</em>, editio altera quam curavit O. Gigon, De Gruyter, Berlin
1961 (repr. of the Berlin 1870 ed.), pp. 837&ndash;944.</li>

<li>Van Campe, L., 2009, &ldquo;Syrianus and Proclus on the Attributes
of the One in Plato&rsquo;s <em>Parmenides</em>&rdquo;, in
<em>Syrianus et la m&eacute;taphysique de l&rsquo;antiquit&eacute;
tardive</em>, A. Longo (ed.), Napoli: Bibliopolis, pp.
247&ndash;80.</li>

<li>van den Berg, R. M., 2001, <em>Proclus&rsquo; Hymns.</em> Leiden:
Brill.</li>

<li>Van Riel, G., 2001, &ldquo;Les h&eacute;nades de Proclus
sont-elles compos&eacute;es de limite et
d&rsquo;illimit&eacute;&#8239;?&rdquo;, <em>Revue des sciences
philosophiques et th&eacute;ologiques</em>, 85: 417&ndash;432.</li>

<li>Verbeke, G., 1981, &ldquo;Aristotle&rsquo;s <em>Metaphysics</em>
Viewed by the Ancient Greek Commentators&rdquo;, in <em>Studies in
Aristotle</em>, D. J. O&rsquo;Meara (ed.), Washington D.C.: The
Catholic University of America Press, pp. 107&ndash;127.</li>

<li>Walz, C., 1832, <em>Rhetores graeci ex codicibus Florentinis,
Mediolanensibus, Monacensibus, Neapolitanis, Parisiensibus, Romanis,
Venetis, Taurinensibus et Vindobonensibus</em>, Osnabr&uuml;ck:
Zeller.</li>

<li>Wildberg, C., 2005, &ldquo;Philosophy in the Age of
Justinian&rdquo;, in <em>The Cambridge Companion to the Age of
Justinian</em>, M. Maas (ed.), Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,
pp. 316&ndash;340</li>
</ul>
</div> 

